items.title: Building social communication skills in shy children helps with peer likeability
items.summary: A new study has discovered that shy children with low English vocabulary skills, can still be popular among their peers if they have high-functioning social communication skills that enable them to engage and interact well with their peers in social settings.

alternate.title: Building social communication skills in shy children helps with peer likeability

items.title: Rolling dice for cell size specification in plant leaf epidermis
items.summary: Scientists have discovered that endoreduplication, which promotes cellular enlargement in the epidermal tissue of Arabidopsis thaliana, occurs randomly as a Poisson process throughout cellular maturation.

alternate.title: Rolling dice for cell size specification in plant leaf epidermis

items.title: More mouths can be fed by boosting number of plant pores
items.summary: Scientists have synthesized a new bioactive small molecule that has the ability to increase stomata numbers on flowering plants without stunting their growth. The team's new discovery could help elucidate the stomatal development mechanism in plants.

alternate.title: More mouths can be fed by boosting number of plant pores
